<dl><dd>Numbers represent direction on a keyboard numpad. For example, <span typeof="mw:File"><span><img alt="236" src="/wiki/images/thumb/7/79/InputIcon_236.png/24px-InputIcon_236.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="24" height="24" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/wiki/images/thumb/7/79/InputIcon_236.png/36px-InputIcon_236.png 1.5x, /wiki/images/thumb/7/79/InputIcon_236.png/48px-InputIcon_236.png 2x"/></span></span>+<span><span class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File"><span><img alt="A" src="/wiki/images/thumb/4/4e/BBCF_A_Prompt.png/22px-BBCF_A_Prompt.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="22" height="22" class="mw-file-element" srcset="/wiki/images/thumb/4/4e/BBCF_A_Prompt.png/33px-BBCF_A_Prompt.png 1.5x, /wiki/images/thumb/4/4e/BBCF_A_Prompt.png/44px-BBCF_A_Prompt.png 2x"/></span></span></span> becomes <span class="colorful-text-4">236A</span>.</dd></dl>
<div class="div-col columns column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 20em; -webkit-column-width: 20em; column-width: 20em;">
<dl><dd><b>></b> = Proceed from the previous move to the following move.</dd>
<dd><b>▷</b>/<b>land</b> = Indicate that the player must land at that point in the sequence.</dd>
<dd><b>,</b> = <span class="tooltip">Link<span class="tooltiptext">To perform a second action after the first action completely finishes its animation.</span></span> the previous move into the following move.</dd>
<dd><b>-></b>/<b>~</b> = <span class="tooltip">Cancel<span class="tooltiptext">To bypass the remaining time or frames in an action by proceeding directly into another action.</span></span> the previous special into a follow-up special.</dd>
<dd><b>dl.</b>/<b>delay</b> = Delay the following move.</dd>
<dd><b>whiff</b>/<b>(whiff)</b> = The move must whiff (not hit).</dd>
<dd><b>c.</b> = Close</dd>
<dd><b>f.</b> = Far</dd>
<dd><b>j.</b> = Jumping/Aerial</dd>
<dd><b>hj.</b>/<b>sj.</b> = High Jump/Super Jump</dd>
<dd><b>jc</b> = <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://glossary.infil.net/?t=Jump%20Cancel">Jump Cancel</a></dd>
<dd><b>hjc</b>/<b>sjc</b> = High Jump Cancel/Super Jump Cancel</dd>
<dd><b>dc</b>/<b>adc</b> = Dash Cancel/Air Dash Cancel</dd>
<dd><b>CH</b> = <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://glossary.infil.net/?t=Counter%20Hit">Counter Hit</a></dd>
<dd><b>AA</b> = <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://glossary.infil.net/?t=Anti-Air">Anti-Air</a></dd>
<dd><b>IAS</b> = <a href="/w/Glossary#Instant_Air_Special" title="Glossary">Instant Air Special</a></dd>
<dd><b>[X]</b> = Hold input.</dd>
<dd><b>]X[</b> = Release input.</dd>
<dd><b>(move)</b> = Move is optional.</dd>
<dd><b>[X] or [Y]</b> = Perform sequence X or Y.</dd>
<dd><b>[sequence] xN</b> = Repeat sequence N amount of times.</dd>
<dd><b>(N)</b> = Hit N of a move or move must deal N amount of hits.</dd>
<dd><b>IAD</b> = Instant Air Dash</dd>
<dd><b>RC</b> = Rapid Cancel</dd>
<dd><b>OD</b> = <a href="/w/BBCF/Mechanics#Overdrive" title="BBCF/Mechanics">Overdrive</a></dd>
<dd><b>ODc / cOD / ODC / OD Cancel</b> = <a href="/w/BBCF/Mechanics#Overdrive_Cancel" title="BBCF/Mechanics">Overdrive Cancel</a></dd>
<dd><b>EA</b> = <a href="/w/BBCF/Mechanics#Exceed_Accel" title="BBCF/Mechanics">Exceed Accel</a></dd></dl>

</section><h2 class="citizen-section-heading"><span class="citizen-section-indicator citizen-ui-icon mw-ui-icon-wikimedia-collapse"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Character_Specifics">Character Specifics</span></h2><section id="citizen-section-2" class="citizen-section">
<p>The <span class="colorful-text-3">3C</span>(1) in air hit <span class="colorful-text-2">6B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">3C</span>(1) must be delayed on the following characters in order to prevent combos from dropping both when midscreen and in the corner: <b>Hazama</b>, <b>Mu</b>, <b>Tager</b>, <b>Terumi</b>, <b>Tsubaki</b>, and <b>Valkenhayn</b>.
</p><p><b>Hakumen</b> and <b>Makoto</b> require that <span class="colorful-text-3">3C</span>(1) is delayed when they're in the corner, though it is not required when they're midscreen.
</p><p>Routes involving <span class="colorful-text-5">5D</span> > <span class="colorful-text-2">5B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-4">236[A]</span>~<span class="colorful-text-5">D</span> will not work on <b>Taokaka</b>, <b>Carl</b>, <b>Relius</b>, <b>Izayoi</b>, <b>Amane</b>, <b>Es</b>, <b>Bullet</b>, and <b>Platinum</b>, due to their hurtbox being <i>just</i> far enough forward to where the activate whiffs. On long starters, this can be remedied by going straight into <span class="colorful-text-2">5B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-4">236[A]</span>~<span class="colorful-text-5">D</span>, but be sure to confirm it quickly
</p><p>Most routes involving <span class="colorful-text-2">6B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">3C</span>(1) > <span class="colorful-text-4">22A</span> will not work on <b>Carl</b>, <b>Tsubaki</b>, <b>Hazama</b>, <b>Mu</b>, <b>Makoto</b>, <b>Valkenhein</b>, <b>Kokonoe</b>, <b>Terumi</b>, <b>Celica</b>, <b>Hibiki</b>, <b>Susan</b>, and <b>Mai</b>, as they dont get popped far enough back for the lightning to hit.
</p><p>Converting without setup after a TK (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://glossary.infil.net/?t=Tiger%20Knee">Tiger Knee</a>) <span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span> using <span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-5">j.5D</span> > <span class="colorful-text-4">j.A</span>(1) > <span class="colorful-text-5">236D</span> isn't possible on <b>Ragna</b>, <b>Makoto</b>, <b>Amane</b>, and <b>Es</b>. Against <b>Noel</b>, <b>Nu</b>, <b>Tsubaki</b>, <b>Hazama</b>, <b>Kagura</b>, <b>Terumi</b>, and <b>Lamda</b>, it will only work in corner.
</p>
</section><h2 class="citizen-section-heading"><span class="citizen-section-indicator citizen-ui-icon mw-ui-icon-wikimedia-collapse"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Combo_Theory">Combo Theory</span></h2><section id="citizen-section-3" class="citizen-section">
<p><span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span> usually requires something covering it (such as a Graviton or a trap) or Kokonoe must spend meter in order to convert it into a full combo. However, in the instances shown below, Kokonoe can combo off <span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span> without help since she'll be able to link <span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span> into <span class="colorful-text-4">5A</span>:
</p>
<ul><li>When Kokonoe lands <span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span> as an air to air with the opponent slightly higher than her</li>
<li>When Kokonoe lands a Fatal Counter TK <span class="colorful-text-3">j.2C</span></li></ul>
<p>When performing any route involving <span class="colorful-text-5">236D</span> > <span class="colorful-text-2">22B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">2C</span> / <span class="colorful-text-4">236[A]</span>, <b>be sure to hold <span class="colorful-text-5">D</span> from <span class="colorful-text-5">236D</span> and release as late as you can</b> (which usually is only for a split second or so, but it'll depend on the hitstun of the move used beforehand. Try to aim for as late into that as possible.) (This will often be notated as "<span class="colorful-text-5">236[D]~]D[</span>", though this applies regardless of how its noted). This is required in many instances of the route, to have enough time to link <span class="colorful-text-2">22B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">2C</span> / <span class="colorful-text-4">236A</span>, or even for instances it's not required will still make the link far more lenient.
</p><p>You're also going to want to learn combos that involve using no Gravitons at all in case you're put into a situation where you don't have any remaining or you don't have enough for a specific combo. Additionally, these 'Gravitonless' combos are better when they are longer since they will give you more time to regenerate any missing Gravitons.
</p>
</section><h2 class="citizen-section-heading"><span class="citizen-section-indicator citizen-ui-icon mw-ui-icon-wikimedia-collapse"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Combo_List">Combo List</span></h2><section id="citizen-section-4" class="citizen-section">

<td>( <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > ) <span class="colorful-text-3">3C</span> > ODC > <span class="colorful-text-2">5B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">3C</span>(1) > <span class="colorful-text-5">5D</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-2">236B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">5C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">2C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">6C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">j2C</span> > <span class="colorful-text-5">236[D]</span> > <span class="colorful-text-2">6B</span> > <span class="colorful-text-4">214214A</span> > <span class="colorful-text-5">5D</span> > <span class="colorful-text-3">236C</span></td>
<td><span class="colorful-text-2">5506</span></td>

</section><h2 class="citizen-section-heading"><span class="citizen-section-indicator citizen-ui-icon mw-ui-icon-wikimedia-collapse"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Golden_Tager_Combos">Golden Tager Combos</span></h2><section id="citizen-section-5" class="citizen-section">
<p>Golden Tager combos require you to know how much health you have left since the less health you have, the more damage you'll be able to get off of it. Remember, the more you spin the stick while holding down the C button, the more damage will be tacked on when Golden Tager fires. Note that <span class="colorful-text-5">6A</span>><span class="colorful-text-5">236[D]</span>~<span class="colorful-text-3">64641236[C]</span>~<span class="colorful-text-5">]D[</span>~<span class="colorful-text-3">]C[</span> combo routes require you to have 40% HP or less, otherwise you'll end up getting regular Dreadnought Destroyer instead.
</p>
<pre><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1MZO_8tcTBTR8mp4e70Y2Labbypj7tTmBnUdtk2LBS4c/edit?usp=sharing">Golden Tager Guide by TempestTim</a>
</pre>
